hank you for any input. <p>Draghixia Bladesong,<B><i> Fallen</B></i> ranger of Surefall Glade. <a href=http://pub49.ezboard.com/bdefendersofvalour>Defenders of Valour</a><Br>"Never mistake the smile on my face as one of joy, I may be contemplating ripping your heart out just to see how long before your body hits the floor." -Me<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulivtinth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Livtinth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Guru</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/31/02 6:08:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1661.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Epic?</span><hr size=1> work on the easy epics that increase your overall damageoutput...monk and rogue...but you won't be able to complete them all alone i think (general for rogue and xenovorash fight for monk will be a problem). raid &quot;easy&quot; zones to get all people to listen to the raid leader and learn the basic raid rules. if you are all casual players, set fix times for raids and schedule at least one or two per week if people can make it. think you will have problems with certain types of raids that require you to have resist gear (but that's a minor issue that can be worked at, make exp groups and hunt gems etc.). but if you work together, i'm sure you can make a lot of good things happen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p><center><img src=http://www.legacyofsteel.net/images/screenshots/december_01/12_30/allakhazam.jpg><br><small><font color=gray><b><a href=http://www.legacyofsteel.net>http://www.legacyofsteel.net</a></small></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><